parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Frame Crossmember Rust and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and failure of the front frame crossmember can cause loss of steering and braking control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls violently to one side when brakes are applied
vehicle shakes or vibrates
loss of steering control
vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
uneven tire wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and corrosion of the body and frame components can cause structural weakness, leading to loss of control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the body
frame
or suspension components
doors
rockers
or floor panels
bubbling or flaking paint
soft or weak spots on the body.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lightweight design and handling characteristics of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in wet weather conditions.
symptoms: Vehicle slides or spins out of control
vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
difficulty staying in lane
vehicle feels unstable or tipsy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alternator Failure Leading to Battery Drain
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leaving the vehicle stranded and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: The battery is dead
the alternator burns up
the vehicle requires frequent repairs
the problem persists after replacing the alternator and car computer.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Malfunction (Wiring Harness, Relay, and Steering Column Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause lights to turn on and off randomly, leading to safety hazards and potential accidents.
symptoms: Parking lights and headlights turn on and off randomly
the wiring harness in the steering column fails
the relay needs to be replaced
the problem persists after repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Lock Cylinder Failure (Key Stuck in Accessory Position)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition lock cylinder can cause the key to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to remove the key, which can lead to safety issues and potential fires.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition switch
the key cannot be removed easily
the car may be in accessory mode or completely off but the key remains.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front differential can cause the 4-wheel drive to slip in and out, leading to loss of traction and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Loud clunking noise in the right front
4-wheel drive slipping in and out
difficulty engaging 4-wheel drive
hard thud sound when shifting out of 4-wheel drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, lock up, or fail to shift properly, leading to accidents or near-accidents.
symptoms: Transmission locks up
fails to shift into gear
skids or sudden stops
whining noise from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and failure of the front suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Violent shuddering of the front suspension
swerving to one side when applying brakes
clunking sounds from the front of the vehicle
front end shimmy at high speeds
and loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy or abnormal brake pedal feel
brake light staying lit
leaking brake fluid
and inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Misrepresentation of warranty coverage can lead to financial losses and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealership or manufacturer representatives providing incorrect information about warranty coverage
failure to cover repairs due to lifted or modified vehicles
and lack of transparency in warranty terms.
